sunFmMIB.name: sunFmMIB
sunFmMIB.contactinfo: Sun Microsystems, Inc. 4150 Network Circle Santa Clara, CA 95054 1-800-555-9SUN or 1-650-960-1300 http://www.sun.com or contact your local support representative

SunFmModuleState.name: SunFmModuleState
SunFmModuleState.description: Represents the status of an fmd(1M) module.

SunFmResourceState.name: SunFmResourceState
SunFmResourceState.description: Represents the status of a system resource as diagnosed by the fault manager.

SunFmEventState.name: SunFmEventState
SunFmEventState.description: Represents the status of a suspect as diagnosed by the fault manager.

sunFmProblemTable.name: sunFmProblemTable
sunFmProblemTable.description: Table listing all of the known problems that have been diagnosed by the fault manager associated with this managed system element that are still present in that system.

sunFmProblemEntry.name: sunFmProblemEntry
sunFmProblemEntry.description: A problem diagnosed by the fault manager and still present in the system.

sunFmProblemUUIDIndex.name: sunFmProblemUUIDIndex
sunFmProblemUUIDIndex.description: The Universal Unique Identifier (UUID) for this problem, as recorded by fmd(1M) and shown by fmadm(1M) or fmdump(1M). This is the index into sunFmProblemTable.

sunFmProblemUUID.name: sunFmProblemUUID
sunFmProblemUUID.description: The Universal Unique Identifier (UUID) for this problem, as recorded by fmd(1M) and shown by fmadm(1M) or fmdump(1M).

sunFmProblemCode.name: sunFmProblemCode
sunFmProblemCode.description: The SUNW-MSG-ID static message identifier for this class of problem, as recorded by fmd(1M) and shown by fmdump(1M). The message identifier can be used as a key at http://sun.com/msg/

sunFmProblemURL.name: sunFmProblemURL
sunFmProblemURL.description: The URL of an appropriate knowledge article providing more detailed information about this problem.

sunFmProblemDiagEngine.name: sunFmProblemDiagEngine
sunFmProblemDiagEngine.description: The Sun FMRI of the Fault Manager diagnosis engine that performed the diagnosis of this problem, including its version.

sunFmProblemDiagTime.name: sunFmProblemDiagTime
sunFmProblemDiagTime.description: The date and time at which the problem was diagnosed.

sunFmProblemSuspectCount.name: sunFmProblemSuspectCount
sunFmProblemSuspectCount.description: The number of individual suspect defects or faults associated with this problem diagnosis, as shown by fmdump(1M) -v -u <UUID>.

sunFmFaultEventTable.name: sunFmFaultEventTable
sunFmFaultEventTable.description: List of individual suspect defects or faults associated with a problem diagnosis, as shown by fmdump(1M) -v -u <UUID>.

sunFmFaultEventEntry.name: sunFmFaultEventEntry
sunFmFaultEventEntry.description: Sun Fault Management fault or defect event containing a suspect problem and the corresponding FRU and ASRU.

sunFmFaultEventUUIDIndex.name: sunFmFaultEventUUIDIndex
sunFmFaultEventUUIDIndex.description: UUID of a problem diagnosis with which this event is associated. An event may appear multiple times in association with different diagnoses. This is an index into sunFmFaultEventTable.

sunFmFaultEventIndex.name: sunFmFaultEventIndex
sunFmFaultEventIndex.description: Index number of this event with respect to the problem diagnosis.

sunFmFaultEventProblemUUID.name: sunFmFaultEventProblemUUID
sunFmFaultEventProblemUUID.description: UUID of a problem diagnosis with which this event is associated. An event may appear multiple times in association with different diagnoses.

sunFmFaultEventClass.name: sunFmFaultEventClass
sunFmFaultEventClass.description: Sun Fault Management event class string.

sunFmFaultEventCertainty.name: sunFmFaultEventCertainty
sunFmFaultEventCertainty.description: Percentage likelihood associated with this suspect for this diagnosis.

sunFmFaultEventASRU.name: sunFmFaultEventASRU
sunFmFaultEventASRU.description: Sun FMRI of the Automated System Reconfiguration Unit (ASRU) that is believed to contain the specified fault or defect.

sunFmFaultEventFRU.name: sunFmFaultEventFRU
sunFmFaultEventFRU.description: Sun FMRI of the Field Replaceable Unit (FRU) that should be replaced in order to repair the specified fault or defect.

sunFmFaultEventResource.name: sunFmFaultEventResource
sunFmFaultEventResource.description: Sun FMRI of the resource responsible for the generation of the telemetry leading to the diagnosis.

sunFmFaultEventStatus.name: sunFmFaultEventStatus
sunFmFaultEventStatus.description: The current status of this suspect for this diagnosis. See fmadm(1M) faulty.

sunFmFaultEventLocation.name: sunFmFaultEventLocation
sunFmFaultEventLocation.description: Label of the Field Replaceable Unit (FRU) that should be replaced in order to repair the specified fault or defect.

sunFmModuleTable.name: sunFmModuleTable
sunFmModuleTable.description: List of modules configured in fmd(1M).

sunFmModuleEntry.name: sunFmModuleEntry
sunFmModuleEntry.description: A module which has been loaded into fmd(1M) to handle events. The information provided is equivalent to the output of fmadm(1) config'

sunFmModuleIndex.name: sunFmModuleIndex
sunFmModuleIndex.description: Unique integer index associated with this fault management module's entry.

sunFmModuleName.name: sunFmModuleName
sunFmModuleName.description: Name of the fault management module.

sunFmModuleVersion.name: sunFmModuleVersion
sunFmModuleVersion.description: Version string associated with the fault management module.

sunFmModuleStatus.name: sunFmModuleStatus
sunFmModuleStatus.description: Current status of the fault management module.

sunFmModuleDescription.name: sunFmModuleDescription
sunFmModuleDescription.description: A text description of the fault management module.

sunFmResourceCount.name: sunFmResourceCount
sunFmResourceCount.description: The number of managed elements currently believed by the fault manager to be faulty.

sunFmResourceTable.name: sunFmResourceTable
sunFmResourceTable.description: A table containing information about all resources for which the fault manager has received telemetry. This is the same information provided by the fmadm(1M) faulty command.

sunFmResourceEntry.name: sunFmResourceEntry
sunFmResourceEntry.description: Information about the state of a resource the fault manager believes to be faulty.

sunFmResourceIndex.name: sunFmResourceIndex
sunFmResourceIndex.description: Index of the resource in the resource table.

sunFmResourceFMRI.name: sunFmResourceFMRI
sunFmResourceFMRI.description: Sun FMRI of the Automated System Reconfiguration Unit (ASRU) which the fault manager believes to be faulty.

sunFmResourceStatus.name: sunFmResourceStatus
sunFmResourceStatus.description: The current status of the resource. See fmadm(1M) faulty.

sunFmResourceDiagnosisUUID.name: sunFmResourceDiagnosisUUID
sunFmResourceDiagnosisUUID.description: The Universal Unique Identifier (UUID) for the problem associated with the fault in this resource, as recorded by fmd(1M) and shown by fmadm(1M).

sunFmObjectGroup.name: sunFmObjectGroup
sunFmObjectGroup.description: A collection of objects providing access to Sun Fault Manager operational data.

sunFmProblemTrap.name: sunFmProblemTrap
sunFmProblemTrap.description: Trap notification that a diagnosis has been made or the fault manager fmd(1M) has restarted and the corresponding problem is still believed to be present in the managed entity.

sunFmNotificationGroup.name: sunFmNotificationGroup
sunFmNotificationGroup.description: A collection of notifications provided by the Sun Fault Manager.
